# Database Rules

## Database Provider

PostgreSQL on Vultr VPS (self-hosted or Vultr Managed PostgreSQL)

## ORM & Driver

- Drizzle ORM
- `pg` (node-postgres) connection pool via `drizzle-orm/node-postgres`

## Primary Keys

- UUID

## Requirements

- Foreign Key Constraints
- Database Indexes
- Soft Deletes when appropriate
- Schema defined in `src/db/schema.ts`
- Migrations managed via Drizzle Kit (`drizzle/migrations/`)

## Never

- Store images inside database
- Store large files inside database
- Duplicate user data
- Use Supabase, Neon, or Firebase clients
- Use raw SQL without Drizzle (except migrations and RLS setup)

## Images

- Cloudflare R2 only

## Tables

- users
- cars
- car_images
- favorites

## Optimize for

- 100,000+ users
- Fast search
- Low cost

All queries must be optimized and indexed. Use Drizzle relational queries where appropriate.

## Connection pool

- Configure via `DATABASE_POOL_MAX` (default 10 per Node process)
- With PM2 single instance, one pool is sufficient
